overview: The three musketeers are a theater performance / musical in two acts written by Alexander MÃ¸rk-Eidem, based on Alexandre Duma's novel The Three Musketeers.  The performance was premiere at the Stockholm City Theater on February 27, 2009 and was played until December 2009. It then had a two-year break due to a rights dispute. Some of the music had to be replaced, including music by Prince, Madonna and Michael Jackson. The three musketeers had a new premiere in March 2012 and were played until September 2012. Sveriges Television (SVT) recorded the musical in autumn 2012 and showed on December 30, 2012.
title: The Three Musketeers - The Musical
